 <svg class="h-7 w-7" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
 <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.75 10.5V6a3.75 3.75 0 10-7.5 0v4.5m11.356-1.993l1.263 12c.07.665-.45 1.243-1.119 1.243H4.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.12-1.243l1.264-12A1.125 1.125 0 015.513 7.5h12.974c.576 0 1.059.435 1.119 1.007zM8.625 10.5a.375.375 0 11-.75 0.375.375 0 01.75 0zm7.5 0a.375.375 0 11-.75 0.375.375 0 01.75 0z" />
 </svg>
 </div>
 <h2 class="mb-4 font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-charcoal sm:text-4xl">Branded Apparel</h2>
 <p class="mb-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ash">
 Full crew uniform programs for construction and the trades. Hi-vis ANSI Class 2 and Class 3. FR-rated tees and shirts (NFPA 70E CAT 1 and CAT 2). Work pants, coveralls, softshell jackets, beanies, and caps. All sourced from brands your foremen already trust — Carhartt, Bulwark, Red Kap, Port Authority, ML Kishigo — and decorated to your spec.
 </p>
 <p class="mb-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-ash">
 We don't just ship you a box of shirts. We help you build a uniform spec that actually holds up: the right weight fabric for summer pours, the right cut for guys in a harness, the right hi-vis class for your job category. If you're running a mixed crew — office staff, field superintendents, tradespeople — we'll put together a tiered catalog so everyone's on-brand without forcing your office manager into a polo she won't wear.
 </p>
 <div class="mb-6 grid grid-cols-3 gap-3">
 <div class="border border-hairline bg-panel p-3">
 <div class="spec text-gold-600">Brands</div>
 <div class="mt-1 font-heading text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-tight text-charcoal">Carhartt, Bulwark+</div>
 </div>
 <div class="border border-hairline bg-panel p-3">
 <div class="spec text-gold-600">Compliance</div>
